defs.docs:
This crate provides a streaming CSV (comma separated values) writer and
 reader that works with the `serialize` crate to do type based encoding
 and decoding. There are two primary goals of this project:

defs.name: index
defs.docs: This sub-module provides experimental CSV record indexing.

defs.docs: A type for representing CSV data with a basic record index.

defs.name: Data
defs.docs: A single CSV field as a borrowed slice of the parser's internal buffer.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs:
A CSV error found during parsing. When an error is found, it is
 first returned. All subsequent calls of `next_bytes` will return
 `EndOfCsv`. (EOF is exempt from this. Depending on the state of the
 parser, an EOF could trigger `Data`, `EndOfRecord` and `EndOfCsv`,
 all in succession.)

defs.name: EndOfRecord
defs.docs: Indicates the end of a record.

defs.name: EndOfCsv
defs.docs:
Indicates the end of the CSV data. Once this state is entered, the
 parser can never leave it.

defs.name: NextField
defs.docs: NextField is the result of parsing a single CSV field.

defs.name: byte_headers
defs.docs:
These are low level methods for dealing with the raw bytes of CSV records.
 You should only need to use these when you need the performance or if
 your CSV data isn't UTF-8 encoded.
